MR CLARK HAD A DIFFERENT PERSPECTIVE ON LIFE.
AS A CHILD MR CLARK'S FATHER TOOK A JOB AS THE HEAD CUSTODIAN FOR A LIBRARY IN HIS TOWN.
MR CLARK'S FAMILY WAS ABLE TO LIVE IN THE LIBRARY BECAUSE HIS FATHER WORKED THERE.
MR CLARK WAS KIND OF EMBARRASSED TO LIVE IN THE LIBRARY AND DIDN'T WANT TO TELL KIDS HE LIVED THERE.
MR CLARK'S FATHER HAD GREAT PRIDE IN HIS WORK AND THE LIBRARY WAS SPOTLESS EVERYDAY.
MR CLARK WOULD NEED TO BE QUITE DURING THE DAY IN THE LIBRARY BUT AT NIGHT WHEN EVERYONE WAS GONE, HE COULD PLAY AND YELL AND RUN AROUND AS MUCH AS HE WANTED.
AT NIGHT, MR. CLARK WOULD LAY IN BED WITH QUESTIONS IN HE HEAD.
TO GET HIS ANSWERS HE WOULD GO DOWN TO THE LIBRARY AND LOOK UP THE ANSWERS TO HIS QUESTIONS.
AS TIME WENT ON, MR CLARK WENT TO COLLEGE AND BECAME A PROFESSOR.
HE WAS VERY PROUD OF WHAT HE HAD BECOME AND ALTHOUGH HIS FATHER WASN'T VERY VOCAL ABOUT IT, HE WAS PROUD OF HIS SON AS WELL.
MR CLARK ALWAYS WONDERS WHAT HIS LIFE WOULD HAVE BEEN LIKE IF HE HADN'T LIVED IN THE LIBRARY.
MR CLARK'S DAD TOOK A JOB AS CUSTODIAN AT THE LOCAL LIBRARY.
BECAUSE MR CLARK'S DAD WORKED AT THE LIBRARY HIS FAMILY WAS ALLOWED TO LIVE IN THE LIBRARY.
MR CLARK WAS SOMEWHAT EMBARRASSED TO LIVE IN THE LIBRARY AND NEVER HAD AN FRIENDS OVER TO VISIT.
DURING THE DAY MR CLARK HAD TO BE QUITE WHILE PEOPLE WERE IN THE LIBRARY BUT AT NIGHT WHEN EVERYONE WHEN HOME HE WAS ABLE TO PLAY AND RUN AROUND.
SOMETIMES AT NIGHT HE WOULD THINK OF A QUESTION AND GO DOWN TO THE LIBRARY TO GET HIS ANSWERS EVEN AT 3AM.
AS TIME WENT ON, MR CLARK WENT TO COLLEGE AND BECAME A PROFESSOR.
HE WAS PROUD OF HIS ACCOMPLISHMENTS AND WHEN HE ASKED HIS DAD WHAT HE THOUGHT, HE KNEW HIS DAD WAS PROUD TOO EVEN IN IS QUIET WAY OF ANSWERING.
